schemaList.FormattedDisplayName: Notify Integrity Event Visa Application Response (V1.0)

description:
Service Usage

This service is published by visa processing systems to notify subscribers when an application has been lodged. The payload is intended to contain information which may be useful for integrity matching (eg. client roles, history, related contacts etc).
readme:
Service Usage

This service is published by visa processing systems to notify subscribers when an application has been lodged. The payload is intended to contain information which may be useful for integrity matching (eg. client roles, history, related contacts etc).

Service Behaviour

This service follows the standard notification pattern. The publisher creates a request messages and receives an acknowledgement from the ESB. There is no message returned from the consumer to the provider.

Transformation

Transformation exists on the ESB between enterprise and ICSE provider messages. Conditional filtering exists based on the permission type, service code or application information.
